import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

%matplotlib inline
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
X = np.atleast_2d(np.linspace(-3,3,100)).T
y = np.sin(X) + np.random.normal(1)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
plt.plot(X,y)

[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7fbed79d4f50>]
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
from thompson_sampling.models import SimpleModel
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
van = OnlineBootstrapEnsemble(SimpleModel,1,100)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
for i in range(1000):
    _ = van.fit_ensemble(X,y)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
outcomes = van.predict_distribution(X)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
plt.plot(X, outcomes['means'])
plt.fill_between(X.squeeze(), outcomes['means'].squeeze(), outcomes['means'].squeeze() + outcomes['stds'].squeeze() ,alpha=0.3)
plt.fill_between(X.squeeze(), outcomes['means'].squeeze(), outcomes['means'].squeeze() - outcomes['stds'].squeeze(), alpha = 0.3 )
plt.plot(X,y)
